### **2. HTTP Endpoint Mapping (MapMcp) - AspNetCore**

**Namespace:** `Microsoft.AspNetCore.Builder`

```csharp
// In Startup/Program.cs
app.MapMcp(string pattern = "/mcp")  // Returns: IEndpointConventionBuilder

// Configure HTTP transport during DI setup
builder.Services
    .AddMcpServer()
    .WithHttpTransport(Action<HttpServerTransportOptions> configureOptions = null)
```

**HttpServerTransportOptions class:**
```csharp
public class HttpServerTransportOptions
{
    // Callback to configure per-session McpServerOptions
    public Func<HttpContext, McpServerOptions, CancellationToken, ValueTask> 
        ConfigureSessionOptions { get; set; }

    // Manual session runner callback
    public Func<HttpContext, IMcpServer, CancellationToken, ValueTask> 
        RunSessionHandler { get; set; }

    // Stateless mode (no per-process session storage)
    public bool Stateless { get; set; } = false;

    // Session timeout
    public TimeSpan IdleTimeout { get; set; } = TimeSpan.FromHours(2);

    // Max idle sessions in memory
    public int MaxIdleSessionCount { get; set; } = 100_000;

    // For testing
    public TimeProvider TimeProvider { get; set; }
}
```

